      • EXTERNAL_CALL_SUCCESS

        public static final String EXTERNAL_CALL_SUCCESS
        Optional exchange property, which can be set during external call execution.
        • If set to true, the external call is considered successful
        • If set to false, the external call is considered failed
        • If not set (default) or set to null, the external call is considered successful unless: either an unhandled exception occurs (Exchange.isFailed() returns true), or the exchange is stopped (Exchange.ROUTE_STOP property is set to true)
        If set to anything else, a boolean value will be acquired via Camel type conversion.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
